The U.S. Regional carrier &lt;MetroAirlines> has signed an agreement with Saab Scania AB &lt;SABS ST>to buy 16 34-seater Saab SF340 aircraft worth a total 650 mlncrowns, the Swedish group's largest single order yet, Saabsaid.    It said in a statement that Metro airlines was also takingan option on a further 15 SF340 commuter planes.    The aircraft are to be delivered between now and nextApril.    "The order from Metro airlines is a definite breakthroughfor the Saab SF340," said Tomy Hjort, the head of the SF340programme at Saab's air division. reuter&#3;